  Key best practices covered include:
  • Prompt Structure ([4:00](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=240s)): Setting the task, providing content, giving detailed instructions, including examples, and repeating important information.
  • Task and Tone Context ([5:36](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=336s)): Clearly defining the model's role and desired tone (e.g., factual and confident).
  • Background Detail and Data ([8:50](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=530s)): Providing static information about the data (like the form structure) in the system prompt.
  • Using Delimiters ([9:53](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=593s)): Employing XML tags or markdown to organize information for Claude.
  • Examples (Few-Shot) ([13:09](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=789s)): Giving the model examples of inputs and desired outputs, especially for tricky scenarios.
  • Conversation History ([15:01](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=901s)): Including past interactions to enrich context (though not used in this specific demo).
  • Detailed Task Lists and Guidelines ([16:06](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=966s)): Guiding Claude through step-by-step reasoning and reminding it of crucial rules (e.g., only answer if confident).
  • Output Formatting ([20:26](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=1226s)): Specifying the desired format for the final output (e.g., using XML tags for the verdict).
  • Pre-filled Responses ([22:25](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=1345s)): Guiding Claude to start its response in a specific format (like JSON).
  • Extended Thinking/Scratchpad ([23:23](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysPbXH0LpIE&t=1403s)): Allowing Claude to show its reasoning process to help refine the prompt.
  
